The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Karim is a satisfied man
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Karim is a satisfied man
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mohun Bagan coach Karim Bencherifa was a satisfied man on Monday. The 1-0 win over Mahindra United was his teams fifth win on the trot in the I-League.         
	I am happy. I cannot ask for more They have done a great job, a happy Bencherifa told reporters after the match. I was too much concerned about this phase The back-to-back matches were tough and I am happy that we have performed well.         
	Asked about his plans for the ensuing match against United SC, the Moroccan coach said: We want to keep the momentum going. Our results talk about our performance Our statistics portray our progress and we would like to maintain this.         
	He, however, complained about the standard of refereeing in the ongoing league.         
	I would like to invite the referees to have a look at the television replays of todays match and then they will realise the errors. I think they need to improve at some point of time, he emphasised.                                                                                                                          
